intro.firstPageLabel: Did you forget what set you were during your workout?
intro.thirdPageLabel: Tell me your sets and how much time you will rest that I'll help you!
intro.fourthPageLabel: Oh! And if there is either an isometrics or an exercise execution time, you can tell me too!

timerPage.setsHelp: This is where you select the total number of sets that will be performed.
timerPage.restHelp: This is where the total duration of rest for each set, in minutes and seconds, is defined.
timerPage.isometricsHelp: This is where the total duration of isometric/execution exercise is defined. Some examples could be a plank (Isometric exercise) or a running (Execution exercise)
timerPage.autoRestHelp: This is where, in case there is either an execution or isometric exercise, you can choose whether the rest time should automatically elapse after the isometric/execution exercise time has ended.
timerPage.stepHelp: These are the exercises that can be either defined or have already been defined. If an exercise has been defined, you can click on the corresponding number to edit it.

exerciseListSettingPage.stepQuantityHelp: This indicates the number of exercises that will be performed.

timeCountPage.timeBeep: When time reaches 10 seconds, it will emit a single beep. During the 3 last seconds, it will once per second.

stepPage.cancelDescription: Do you really want to stop setting your exercises?

exerciseTimer.cancelDescription: Do you really want to stop the current exercise?

notification.executionFinishedBody: Execution/isometric exercise finished. Let's rest of set

closeAppDescription: Do you really want to close your counting?
